{"article_id":"IBf1eu0p8MOgAseE","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"New York","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"( CNN Business )","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"After a barrage of criticism , the New York Times said Sunday","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"it was deeply sorry","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"about publishing an anti-Semitic cartoon","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"depicting Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu as a dog on a leash","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"held by a blind President Donald Trump .","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"It is promising `` significant changes '' in its decision making process in the wake of the embarrassment .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"The cartoon appeared in the opinion section of the international print edition of the paper next to a column by Thomas Friedman about immigration .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"The Times apology came Sunday afternoon","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"after it issued an earlier statement","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"it was wrong to run a cartoon","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that contained `` anti-Semitic tropes . ''","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"But that statement did not contain any apology .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"The new statement said :","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"`` We are deeply sorry for the publication of an anti-Semitic political cartoon last Thursday in the print edition of The New York Times","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"that circulates outside of the United States ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"and we are committed to making sure","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"nothing like this happens again . ''","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"`` Such imagery is always dangerous ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and at a time","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"when anti-Semitism is on the rise worldwide ,","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"it 's all the more unacceptable , ''","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"it continued .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"The paper said","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"the decision","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"to run the syndicated cartoon","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"was made by a single editor","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"working","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"without adequate oversight .","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"`` The matter remains under review ,","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"and we are evaluating our internal processes and training , ''","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"said the statement .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"`` We anticipate significant changes . ''","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"`` The image was offensive ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"and it was an error of judgment to publish it .","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"It was provided by The New York Times News Service and Syndicate ,","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"which has since deleted it , ''","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"said the initial statement from the Times ,","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"which it disclosed in a tweet","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"and said","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"would appear in the print edition of the paper on Monday .","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"An Editors ' Note to appear in Monday 's international edition .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"pic.twitter.com/1rl2vXoTB","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"3 - New York Times Opinion","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"( @ nytopinion )","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"April 27 , 2019","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"`` Apology not accepted .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"How many New York Times editors looked at a cartoon","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"that would not have looked out of place on a white supremacist website","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"and thought","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"it met the paper 's editorial standards ?","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"What does this say about your processes or your decision makers ?","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"How are you fixing it ? ''","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"tweeted the American Jewish Committee .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"Apology not accepted .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"How many @ nytimes editors looked at a cartoon","depth":15},{"id":58,"text":"that would not have looked out of place on a white supremacist website","depth":15},{"id":59,"text":"and thought","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"it met the paper 's editorial standards ?","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"What does this say about your processes or your decision makers ?","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"How are you fixing it ?","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"https : //t.co/HD5LdeZ9z3","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"- AJC","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"( @ AJCGlobal )","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"April 27 , 2019","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"David Harris , the CEO of the AJC , also condemned the Times and its lack of a full apology .","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"`` No , 'apology ' is n't adequate .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Rather , [ the New York Times ] owes readers an explanation","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"of how this happened","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"- after all , decision","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"to print","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"it involved more than one person -","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"& what it says about the paper 's view of Israel & Jews , ''","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"he wrote in one tweet .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"`` While # Antisemitism is rising ...","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"synagogues are attacked","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"& Jews killed ...","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"democratic # Israel is demonized ...","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"& Jewish institutions are forced to bolster security ...","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"The 'paper of record ' pours oil on the fire , ''","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"he said in another .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"The more I think about the @ nytimes `` cartoon ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"'' the more appalled I am .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"While # Antisemitism is rising ...","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"synagogues are attacked","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"& Jews killed ...","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"democratic # Israel is demonized ...","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"& Jewish institutions are forced to bolster security ...","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"The `` paper of record '' pours oil on the fire .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"pic.twitter.com/8FUAEKCagK","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"- David Harris","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"( @ DavidHarrisAJC )","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"April 27 , 2019","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"Most staffers","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"who work in the United States for The Times","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"did not know about the image in the international editions","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"until they read about the editor 's note on Saturday ,","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"according to three Times staffers","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"who requested anonymity .","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"They were alarmed","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"to see the image in the first place","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"-- and dismayed","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"that the initial explanation was so feeble .","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"The cartoon , and the Times ' attitude towards Israel , was criticized in a column","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"posted Sunday by Bret Stephens , one of the paper 's op-ed columnists .","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"He said","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"he is certain","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"that the Times is not guilty of institutional anti-Semitism .","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"But he said","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"the cartoon was a sign of the Times ongoing criticism of Zionism and the Israeli government .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"`` The almost torrential criticism of Israel and the mainstreaming of anti-Zionism ,","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"including by this paper , ...","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"has become so common","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"that people have been desensitized to its inherent bigotry , ''","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"he wrote .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"And he argued","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"that `` anti-Zionism is all but indistinguishable from anti-Semitism in practice and often in intent ,","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"however much progressives try to deny this . ''","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"The cartoon and the initial lack of apology was also criticized by White House counselor Kellyanne Conway in an appearance on `` State of the Union '' on CNN on Sunday .","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"`` This anti-Semitic cartoon","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"which I 'm not even going to describe the particulars","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"because it is so odious and offensive ,","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"they did n't even apologize for it , ''","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"she said Sunday morning ahead of the Times ' second statement .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"`` Apologies usually include words like regret , sorry and apologize .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"They did n't do that . ''","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"CNN host Jake Tapper agreed with her statement .","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"And the cartoon , and the Times response , also came under criticism on Reliable Sources on CNN on Sunday .","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"`` We 're talking about normalizing hate speech .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"The New York Times only aids in that","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"when it publishes cartoons","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"and gives this meek , silly little statement of 'regret ' about it , ''","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"said Elaina Plott , White House correspondent for The Atlantic ,","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"as she used her fingers","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"to indicate quote marks around the word regret .","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"She said","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"it 's important for the Times to be far more transparent","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"and to issue a detailed statement","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"about how the mistake","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"to run the cartoon","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"was made .","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":285,"left":0,"right":284,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":284,"left":236,"right":283,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":236,"left":150,"right":235,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":1,"right":149,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":149,"left":148,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":147,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":2,"right":146,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":3,"right":145,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":4,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":207,"right":234,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":207,"left":155,"right":206,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":9,"right":154,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":153,"right":14,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":10,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":11,"right":151,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":164,"right":205,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":159,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":15,"right":158,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":158,"left":156,"right":157,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":156,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":162,"right":24,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162